        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>It is no trouble to me to write short notes. I sent off duplicates this morning of 2 finally corrected sheets; &amp; shall soon be able to send more.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>There is a difficulty about the Heliotype Co<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>. as they want to charge <hi rend="doubleUnderline">far</hi> more than their printed estimate; &amp; I do not know how we shall agree, but I will inform you as soon as I hear.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>We leave home for 8 days on Tuesday morning, as I am quite done up.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>My book will now be finished very soon.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I am sorry to say that I have never even heard of the book to which you refer.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Before you leave England pray come &amp; lunch or dine here; I shall be most happy to see you.—<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. I see I have forgotten to say, that the sole verbal agreement which I wish to make with you is that you shall give me some moderate percentage of any <hi rend="underline">clear</hi> profits which you may make.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
