        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD was sending Kovalevsky the proof-sheets of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> for his Russian translation of the work (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8459.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from V. O. Kovalevsky, 8 August [1872]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8463.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. F. Cooke, 10 August [1872]</ref> and n. 2.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD was at Leith Hill Place in Surrey, the home of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5027.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Josiah Wedgwood III</ref> and Caroline Sarah Wedgwood, from 13 to 21 August 1872 (‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD finished correcting the proof-sheets of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> on 22 August 1872 (‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8524.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Wundt 1863</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8459.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from V. O. Kovalevsky, 8 August [1872]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Kovalevsky visited CD on 22 September 1872 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>
        </div>        
            
